Creating Models: Linear Regression

Maximilian Weissenbacher

9 7 2021

Create Models out of the obtained data

The key goal of this project is to estimate the price of a car

In the “Data Cleaning & Understanding” markdown file all of the variables got observed.

The variables which might have an influence on the price are: - Kraftstoff (fuel type) - Marke (car make) - Hubraum (engine sizte; in strong Correlation to PS) - PS (horsepower) - KM (kilometers driven) - Alter (age of the car) - Fahrzeughalter (number of car owners)

clean_cars <- read.csv("cleaned_cars1.csv")

Create Train/Test Set

all_cars <- clean_cars[complete.cases(clean_cars), ]
train.index <- createDataPartition(all_cars$preis, list = FALSE, p = 0.75)
train <- all_cars[train.index, ]
test <- all_cars[-train.index, ]
nrow(test)
## [1] 7839
nrow(train)
## [1] 23520

Create different models

# Just test on clean_cars. When all data is scraped use Train/Test

  • The Residuals vs. Fitted Plot shows in this case that the model doesn’t have non-linear relationships.
  • Normal QQ Plot: Normal distribution is not given because the points don’t follow the increasing line at the start and the tail
  • Scale-Location Plot: residuals aren’t spread equally along the ranges of predictors, because the line is increasing and it should be horizontal in an optimal case
